title: Myles Standish State Park Road Race
Massasoit Lung Opener
description: The return of the Massasoit Lung Opener Mountain Bike Race from the 1990â€™s was a long time coming but is now back as a fundraiser for the American Lung Association. The traditional spring race works well with the sand based soil of cranberry land and has a tendency to dry out much quicker than other parts of New England.
course: The 7.1  mile course is a large clockwise loop with lots of fun single track, some fast double track and a very limited amount of smooth pavement. The terrain is most difficult in the early part of the loop before becoming more rolling in the middle with a couple of short kickers at the end.
registration: On line Registraiton is available on BikeReg.com. Day of registration will be located near the gatehouse on the paved road entering the Park.
notes:
It\'s a great course rain OR shine.
Pre-rides before race day encouraged.
directions:
Massasoit State Park

East Taunton, MA  02718

title: Blue Hills Classic
description: The Blue Hills Classic is an annual bike race held each Spring in the Blue Hills Reservation in Milton MA. Proceeds support local and State charitable organizations.
course: The course is a 7.2 mile loop around Great Blue Hill in Milton.  There is a 2 mile climb in the loop.  Racers will complete multiple laps depending on their race category and will finish at the top of the climb on Unquity Road on their last lap.
registration: Registration will be available online thru BikeReg.  No refunds.  Day of registration will be available and opens at 7am.  Day of registration closes 1/2 hour before each race.
notes: SRAM wheel support.  Cash payouts place 1-5 ($150,$125,$100,$75,$50).  All prizes awarded at registration area within 30min after a race and results have been approved by race officials.  All USCF rules apply.
directions: Parking/Registration/Staging and Start are located at the main parking lot of Houghton\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\'s Pond on Hillside Street in Milton.  From Rte. 128/93:  take exit 2 (Rte 138N/Milton). Take a right on Blue River Road.  At stop sign continue straight onto Hillside Street.  Entrance to parking lot will be on your right.
